column5: Got this sent to me on FB. Apparently been around since 2017. Anybody know anything about them?
It’s a snowdog clone don’t need insurance or license it has its place, real good for early ice and late ice
Appear to be a bunch cheaper than the Snow dog.
Do you mean price or quality edit: never mind I look at the price of a new snowdog. Wow the price sure went crazy

I think the husky was around a long time ago, but just came back into production. I could be wrong, but there used to be a similar unit called a husky back in the day. Either way, for the price of either, you could have a decent used sled.  S.
Yup I remember that one well, rode on some of them back in the day

Last winter off the 9th, I seen some oldies . They were owned by some russian fellas. These things were not new. If you youtube russian ice fishing sleds,you will see some real neat rides for ice fishing.

Buy used or buy new? Buy on the word of an individual or buy from a manufacturer that must give some form of warrantee. Any machine can break; but for a purpose built machine why not go new? Just questions not a rebuttal.

I'd buy a used sled. Way more versatile, and much better unit. I've used the snowdog, and they are OK for going A to B on the lake, but hit a hill, or slight slope coming off the lake, and they turn into a nightmare pretty quick. Just my opinion, but I'm not a fan.  S.
